{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b6f6f7d6-9b9e-44cb-b9b3-4ee197741886","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Tests appear as \"new\" in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default Fully Qualified Name (FQN) format** used as the test ID. Azure DevOps matches test history by this ID, so all tests look new. Fix by opting into the legacy format in your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<MSTest>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</MSTest>\n```\n\nOr accept the new IDs and let history rebuild over time.\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level context** — it no longer has a valid `TestName` (there's no specific test running yet). Accessing it throws. Your `SetupTests.ClassInit` on line 13 hits exactly this.\n\n**Fix:** Remove or guard the `TestName` access in `ClassInit`. If you need the name, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]`.\n\n## 3. Other key v4 breaking changes to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Implicit type conversions (e.g., `int` → `long`) no longer happen; supply the exact type. |\n| **Test parallelism** | Default is now parallel at the **method** level. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` if your tests share class state. |\n| **`Assert.AreEqual` for collections** | No longer accidentally works on collections; use `CollectionAssert` instead. |\n| **`[DeploymentItem]`** | Behavior tightened — relative paths resolve differently. |\n| **Removed APIs** | Several deprecated members (e.g., some `TestContext` properties like `DataConnection`) are gone. |\n\nWould you like me to patch `SetupTests.cs` to move the `TestName` usage into a `[TestInitialize]` method?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"556a54d9-02e2-48f0-b533-8d868ff1a518","outputTokens":504,"requestId":"4809:286947:60F827F:6974FCF:69FC010F"},"id":"af897be1-c94d-4f36-ae6f-2170a49588f5","timestamp":"2026-05-07T03:03:57.332Z","parentId":"bedade00-8f8a-404d-a192-593bc131f137"}
